Definition: lose clarity or turn aside especially from the main subject of attention or course of argument in writing, thinking, or speaking
Example: She always digresses when telling a story; her mind wanders; Don't digress when you give a lecture
Synonyms: adj, all, indirect, digressive, noun, communication, digression, act, stray, divagate, divagation, wander, tell, lose, clarity, or, turn, aside, especially, from, the, main, subject, of, attention, course, argument, in, writing, thinking, speaking, She, always, digresses, when, telling, a, story, her, mind, wanders, Don, t, you, give, lecture
Frame: 2,22
Category: verb.communication
